JEREMIAH HILL, PROSECUTOR, v. CITY OF BAYONNE, RESPONDENT. Decided October 7, 1924.

Before Justices Kalisch, Black and Campbell.

For the prosecutor, Bichard Doherty. For the respondent, Eugene T. Sharkey. Memorandum,

The posecutor having failed to file his brief, the writ of certiorari is dismissed, with costs, for lack of prosecution.
